OPERATE IN ACCORDANCE WITH AND HAVE THE EFFECT REQUIRED BY Article III, §
52 of the Maryland Constitution.
3–501.
(a) (1) The following individuals or entities shall designate one or more
representatives to participate as a party in collective bargaining on behalf of the State or
the following institutions:
(i) on behalf of the State, the Governor;
(ii) on behalf of the Maryland Environmental Service, the Board of
Directors of the Service;
(iii) on behalf of the University System of Maryland, the Chancellor;
and
(iv) on behalf of Morgan State University, St. Mary’s College of
Maryland, or Baltimore City Community College, the governing board of the institution.
(2) The exclusive representative shall designate one or more
representatives to participate as a party in collective bargaining on behalf of the exclusive
representative.
(b) (1) [The] SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE
parties shall meet at reasonable times [and] BETWEEN JULY 1 AND SEPTEMBER 30 TO
engage in collective bargaining in good faith[, including facilitating the meaningful use of
a fact finder under subsection (c)(3) of this section,] and to conclude a written memorandum
of understanding or other written understanding as defined under § 3–101(d)(1)(i)2 of this
title.
(2) (I) THIS PARAGRAPH DOES NOT APPLY TO:
– 3 –

Ch. 156 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
1. A BARGAINING UNIT IN A STATE INSTITUTION OF
HIGHER EDUCATION, INCLUDING THE UNIVERSITY SYSTEM OF MARYLAND; OR
2. A BARGAINING UNIT FOR THE UNIFORMED FIRE
EMPLOYEES OF THE BWI AIRPORT FIRE AND RESCUE DEPARTMENT.
(II) 1. FOR EACH BARGAINING UNIT, WHENEVER A
MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING IS TO BE NEGOTIATED, REOPENED, OR
AMENDED, EITHER PARTY MAY REQUEST A NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR FOR THE
NEGOTIATIONS ON OR AFTER JULY 1.
2. IF NEGOTIATIONS HAVE NOT CONCLUDED BY
SEPTEMBER 1, THE PARTIES SHALL SELECT A NEUTRAL ARBITRATOR ON OR BEFORE
SEPTEMBER 15.
(III) THE ARBITRATOR SHALL BE SELECTED FROM A LIST OF 15
ARBITRATORS PROVIDED BY THE AMERICAN ARBITRATION ASSOCIATION’S LABOR
ARBITRATION PANEL.
(IV) THE LIST SHALL CONSIST OF QUALIFIED, NATIONWIDE
ARBITRATORS WHO ARE MEMBERS OF THE NATIONAL ACADEMY OF ARBITRATION.
(V) THE PARTIES SHALL SELECT THE ARBITRATOR BY
ALTERNATELY STRIKING NAMES FROM THE LIST UNTIL ONE NAME REMAINS.
(VI) THE SELECTED ARBITRATOR MUST BE ABLE AND
AVAILABLE TO PERFORM THE DUTIES AND TO HOLD HEARINGS, BOTH IN PERSON
AND THROUGH REMOTE COMMUNICATION, CONSISTENT WITH THIS TITLE.
(VII) THE ARBITRATOR SHALL HAVE THE POWERS AND
RESPONSIBILITIES UNDER § 3–503 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
(VIII) THE SELECTED ARBITRATOR SHALL ACCEPT THE
APPOINTMENT BY THE EARLIER OF SEPTEMBER 30 OR 15 DAYS AFTER THE DAY A
PARTY REQUESTS AN ARBITRATOR BE SELECTED, OR THE PARTIES MAY AGREE TO
MAKE AN ALTERNATIVE APPOINTMENT FROM:
1. THE LIST ORIGINALLY PROVIDED BY THE AMERICAN
ARBITRATION ASSOCIATION; OR
2. A LIST OF NATIONWIDE ARBITRATORS PROVIDED BY
THE FEDERAL MEDIATION AND CONCILIATION SERVICE.
– 4 –

